node.text: The latest trend in cushions is rectangular shaped cushions. From small mini rectangles on a small armchair, to mid sized rectangles on a sofa and jumbo sized ones for beds they are a trend set to stay for the long term. I love using them in combination with square shaped cushions, they look so chic layered up and are a great way to add more pattern and texture without taking up too much sitting space on your furniture. #designtrends #cushions

node.text: The beautiful abbey ruin @painshill -the Ruined Abbey sits wistfully by the water’s edge and casts stunning reflections into the serpentine lake. In the 18th century monasteries and abbeys would often produce wine so the architecture compliments the vineyard planted next to it. It was designed to be a ruin to add an air of history and remind the visitor of the past. If you’re looking for a day out this is a beautiful place to spend the day- beautiful views across Surrey and it has a little playground for kids too. Last weekend we went here in the morning then lunch @grappelli_cobham which was the perfect balance of kids activities and a nice lunch for the adults! #painshill #cobham #weekend #thingstodo #daysoutwithkids no ads or gifts just my experience ✨

node.text: Thanks for all your recommendations on Cheltenham yesterday- I came here for a mini break with two of my sisters and we had a great time. We had a delicious lunch at @kiboucheltenham - which we visited based on advice gratefully received here and we had a delicious dinner @bhoomikitchen_ which my sister @wildwoodlondon had researched- at both places the food and service were great. We stayed @no131cheltenham which was a great location, and had nice staff, only downside is the air con wasn’t working on the first night 🥵, we were on the top floor and they didn’t have any mineral water which was odd, kept saying they’d sold out 🤪 we visited @ivycheltenham for icecream and the building is beautiful- has a stunning domed ceiling. Apart from that we walked all around Montpellier, visiting boutiques and art galleries and had a lovely time #cheltenham - no ads of gifts just my opinion.

node.text: Little details never go unnoticed. I remember when I first visited my in-laws home in Edinburgh back in 2004 they had monogrammed hand towels in their guest loo with a P for Paterson and it always stayed with me how chic this was. So to now have a monogrammed linen collection is something that gives me so much happiness- not only seeing them in our bathrooms at home but also seeing them in clients and friends homes and of course here on Instagram too. Details like this really elevate the every day if you have an eye for it.
